Hypothesis: At small sequence lengths, communication time dominates → algorithm choice matters more.

The results I am getting is not following the hypothesis but what I have observe that while increasing the sequence length the communication grows but the computation also grows but not at the same scale rate as of the communication. I have created the workload for different sequence length tested on ring and get the results.



Commands to run:
cd ~/Desktop/SimAI/aicb

1. For sequence length: 128
python3 -m workload_generator.SimAI_training_workload_generator \
  --model_name GPT --frame Megatron \
  --world_size 8 --tensor_model_parallel_size 4 --pipeline_model_parallel 1 \
  --global_batch 8 --micro_batch 1 \
  --num_layers 2 --hidden_size 2048 --num_attention_heads 8 \
  --seq_length 128 --epoch_num 1
 
 2. For sequence length: 256 
